# Page Implementation Standards

Every public page must have:
- Clear page purpose
- Premium hero/header
- Primary CTA
- Secondary CTA where useful
- Mobile-first responsive layout
- SEO metadata
- Semantic headings
- Relevant trust elements
- Clear next action
- Footer navigation

Required primary pages:
- Home
- Custom Shirts
- Trousers
- Denim
- Weddingwear
- Statement Pieces
- Instagram Looks
- Fit Guide / Weavers Fit Studio
- How It Works
- Book Consultation
- Delivery
- Returns & Alterations
- Contact
- Track Order

CTA mapping:
- Home: Start a Custom Order / Book a Styling Consultation
- Custom Shirts: Customize a Shirt
- Trousers: Customize Trousers
- Denim: Design Your Denim
- Weddingwear: Book Wedding Consultation
- Statement Pieces: Create a Statement Piece
- Instagram Looks: Recreate This Look
- Fit Guide: Start Fit Guide
- Contact: WhatsApp / Send Inquiry

Page acceptance criteria:
- Page looks premium on desktop.
- Page looks polished on mobile.
- CTAs route somewhere meaningful.
- No dead links unless intentionally marked.
- Copy matches Weavers positioning.
- Page does not over-position the brand as Indian clothing only.
- Page is not just static decoration; it supports a user action.
